// archipelago.xs
// =============================================================================
// Archipelago Multiworld integration â€" main XS runtime for Age of Mythology: Retold
// =============================================================================
//
// This is the in-game half of the APâ†"AoMR bridge.  The Python AP client
// (aom/client/GameClient.py) generates `aom_state.xs` from slot_data; that
// file is `#include`d by ap_init.xs alongside this one, providing the
// concrete data tables (gAPItems[], generated APInit*() functions, etc.)
// that the rules below operate on.
//
// HOW THE GAME REACHES IT
// -----------------------
//   1. Every scenario's editor adds a single XS Code Snippet near scenario
//      start:
//        trQuestVarSet("APScenarioID", <scenario_number>);
//        xsEnableRule("APActivateScenario");
//   2. APActivateScenario fires once, dispatches all per-scenario setup
//      (APSetPlayerCiv, APInitItems, APApplyAgeUnlocks, etc.), then enables
//      APApplyItems which finishes applying received items to the running
//      player.
//   3. Rules tagged `inactive` only run when explicitly enabled â€" see the
//      `xsEnableRule(...)` calls scattered through APActivateScenario and
//      APApplyItems.
//
// HIGH-LEVEL ARCHITECTURE
// -----------------------
//   * gAPScenarioId / gAPCampaignId / gAPMajorGod  â€" runtime identity globals
//   * gAPItems[] â€" flag bytes (indices 0-8) + received item ids (index 9..),
//     populated by `APInitItems()` (generated by GameClient.py).
//   * Generated functions consumed by this file (all live in aom_state.xs):
//       APInitItems, APInitGods, APInitGodPowers, APApplyMinorGodSelection,
//       APInitArchaicForbids, APShopStateInit, ...
//   * Player 12 is reserved for trap god powers; cast god powers from P12
//     so the trap fires "from outside" without breaking ally relations.
//
// EXTENDING â€" quick references
// -----------------------------
//   * NEW SCENARIO        : Editor sets APScenarioID + xsEnableRule above.
//                           Add per-scenario branches here only when the
//                           scenario has unique behavior (heroes, victory
//                           conditions, scripted events).  Map the scenario
//                           into APGetCampaignForScenario,
//                           APGetMajorGodForScenario, APGetStartingAgeCount,
//                           and the campaign-section dispatchers below.
//   * NEW MAJOR GOD       : Add cAPMajor<Name> const, extend APSetPlayerCiv,
//                           APApplyAgeUnlocks, APInitGodPowers, and the god
//                           announce/forbid logic.
//   * NEW MINOR GOD       : Add cTechClassicalAge<Name> / cTechHeroicAge<Name>
//                           etc constants below, extend APForceDisableAll<Civ>
//                           and APDisableAll<Civ>AgeTechs.  Free sample myth
//                           units come automatically with the tech.
//   * NEW PANTHEON / CIV  : Largest extension â€" see the header in
//                           aom/__init__.py for the full checklist.  Within
//                           this file you'll need new APForceDisableAll<Civ>,
//                           APDisableAll<Civ>, APApply<Civ>MinorGods, and
//                           dispatch hooks in APApplyAgeUnlocks /
//                           APSetPlayerCiv.
//   * NEW ITEM EFFECT     : Add a branch in APApplyItems where it switches
//                           on the item id (search for cTRAP_*, cSTARTING_ARMY_*,
//                           etc. for examples).  Define handler functions
//                           above the rule.
//   * NEW TRAP            : 1) Add cAPTrap<Name> const matching the Python
//                           `Trap.trap_type`.  2) Add a god-power dispatch
//                           branch in APTrapTimer / ap_ai_runtime.xs.
//
// CONVENTIONS
// -----------
//   * Functions named APForceDisableAll<X>AgeTechs unconditionally clear
//     status to 0; APDisableAll<X>AgeTechs are guarded by trTechStatusActive
//     so they only clear inactive ones.  See the call sites in
//     APApplyAgeUnlocks for context.
//   * `aiEcho()` lines whose body starts with "AP_CHECK:", "AP_LOCKED:",
//     "AP_SHOP:", "AP_TRAP_FIRED:", "AP_RAND_GP:" are tail-parsed by
//     GameClient.py â€" DON'T change those prefixes without updating
//     `read_new_checks` in lock-step.
//   * Most rules end with `xsDisableSelf();` after firing once.  Long-running
//     watchers (APRelicTrickleEnforce, APEnforceAgeLocks, etc.) stay enabled.
//
// Do not include this directly. Use ap_init.xs instead.
// =============================================================================

// extern globals â€" visible across all XS source files including aom_state.xs
extern int gAPItemCount = 0;
// Pre-determined random god powers for the current scenario, populated by
// APInitGodPowers() in aom_state.xs from slot_data on every scenario load.
